# Operator Runbook

This runbook provides essential information and procedures for daily operations of the Automation Platform.

## Overview
The operator runbook contains all the information needed to successfully operate and maintain the automation platform on a day-to-day basis.

## Quick Links
- [Daily Operations Tasks](daily_tasks) - Start here for daily checklist
- [Troubleshooting Guide](troubleshooting) - Common issues and solutions
- [Escalation Procedures](escalation) - When and how to escalate issues

## Responsibilities
As an operator, you are responsible for:
- Monitoring system health and performance
- Responding to alerts and incidents
- Executing daily operational tasks
- Following escalation procedures when needed
- Maintaining accurate documentation and logs

## Getting Started
1. Review the [Daily Operations Tasks](daily_tasks) each morning
2. Check the monitoring dashboard for any alerts
3. Review overnight automation job results
4. Follow up on any pending issues from previous shifts

For troubleshooting help, see the [Troubleshooting Guide](troubleshooting).
For escalation guidance, see [Escalation Procedures](escalation).

